# Control plane vs. compute plane

- Control plane (Databricks-managed) — UI, notebook/SQL editors, job scheduler, cluster manager, UC metadata
- Compute plane — clusters & SQL warehouses that actually process your data with Spark
- Classic compute runs in YOUR cloud account & network; serverless runs in Databricks' account
- Data at rest always stays in your own cloud object storage — never in the control plane
- Serverless = instant start, managed network; classic = your network, tighter isolation
